value.title: Trump said Portland's sheriff supports him. The sheriff disputes that.
value.excerpt: "In tonight's presidential debate the President said the 'Portland Sheriff' supports him. As the Multnomah County Sheriff I have never supported Donald Trump and will never support him," Sheriff Mike Reese tweeted.

value.title: Matt Gorman: Trump has a new running mate now
value.excerpt: Yes, Vice President Mike Pence is still around. And no, the near-constant chatter about former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley did not come to pass.

value.title: Sheriff in Portland denies Trump's debate claim of winning his endorsement
value.excerpt: The sheriff of Multnomah County, which includes Portland, Ore., emphatically denied supporting President Trump Tuesday evening shortly after the president made the claim.

value.title: Undecided voters call Trump ‘unhinged’ and ‘un-American’ — but unswayed by debate
value.excerpt: After watching the first presidential debate Tuesday night, undecided voters from battleground states across the country still had plenty they wanted to know about coronavirus, racial injustice and what each candidate would do to unite the country.

value.title: Biden: 'He's the racist'
value.excerpt: During the first presidential debate, President Donald Trump claimed he ended racial sensitivity training because it was "racist" and Joe Biden responded that Trump is the racist.

value.title: Ross asked if ending census earlier would produce numbers in Trump's current term
value.excerpt: Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross' surprise decision Monday evening to end 2020 census counting on October 5 risks an incomplete tally of as many as 10 states, including Florida and Georgia, according to Census Bureau officials.

value.title: 'Borat' sequel -- with Pence name in title -- to be released before 2020 election by Amazon
value.excerpt: The 2006 original film, written and produced by Cohen, follows the titular character, a Kazakh television personality, as he explores America.

value.title: Trump campaign says president has ‘continuously denounced’ white supremacists, amid criticism
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign on Tuesday told Fox News that President Trump has “continuously denounced” white supremacists, including during the first presidential debate, when they say he did so “twice.”

value.title: Dana Perino's debate verdict: 'Biden cleared the very low bar that had been set for him'
value.excerpt: Democrats concerned about Joe Biden's performance on a debate stage could breathe a sigh of relief Tuesday night following the fractious and bad-tempered first confrontation in Cleveland, former White House press secretary Dana Perino said.

value.title: 'The road to victory goes straight through Pa': VP Pence amps up campaign in Lititz
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence made a campaign stop in Lititz on Tuesday, Sept. 29 to host a presidential debate watch party.

value.title: Trump on Supreme Court overturning Roe v. Wade: 'There's nothing happening there'
value.excerpt: President Trump said Tuesday night there’s “nothing happening” in the Supreme Court with Roe v. Wade, and it isn’t on the ballot with the latest Supreme Court vacancy.

value.title: Philly firefighters, paramedics union breaks with IAFF to endorse Trump
value.excerpt: The firefighters and paramedics union in Philadelphia broke with the International Association of Fire Fighters to endorse President Trump in the upcoming election, according to a report.

value.title: Borat's Mike Pence-Targeting Sequel to Screen on Amazon Prime Ahead of Election Day
value.excerpt: Amazon Prime recently acquired Borat's sequel and is planning to air Sasha Baron Cohen's latest mockumentary at the end of October.

value.title: Joe Biden and his wife, Jill, paid nearly $300,000 in federal income taxes, newly released returns show
value.excerpt: The release served as a contrast to President Trump, after new reports that he has paid minimal or no federal taxes in recent years.

value.title: Netanyahu says Trump’s critics ‘dead wrong’ on Middle East peace efforts
value.excerpt: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Tuesday that President Trump’s critics were “dead wrong,” in predicting that the Trump administration’s attempts to bring peace to the Middle East would fail -- after a series of landmark U.S.-brokered deals were signed this month.

value.title: UFC's Jorge Masvidal to join Donald Trump Jr. for 'Fighters Against Socialism' bus tour
value.excerpt: “The anti communism bus tour will be arriving at a city near you,” Masvidal tweeted.

value.title: Trump's spy chief just released 'Russian disinformation' against Hillary Clinton that he acknowledged may be fabricated
value.excerpt: DNI John Ratcliffe said in a letter that the US intel community "does not know the accuracy" of the allegation or whether it's been fabricated.

value.title: Jill Biden shuts down question about husband's gaffes: 'You can't even go there'
value.excerpt: Asked by CNN's Jake Tapper about Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden's reputation for sometimes misspeaking, Jill Biden said: 'You cannot even go there'

value.title: Don’t be like Trump: Deducting hairstyling and home expenses from your taxes could get you in trouble with the IRS
value.excerpt: Trump tax returns confirm that the rich are different from you and me. So, no, you cannot deduct the cost of getting your hair cut and styled

value.title: Jewish group compares Trump administration to 1930s Nazi Germany
value.excerpt: The Jewish Democratic Council for America compared the nation under President Trump to Germany under Adolf Hitler in the 1930s in a new ad targeting Jewish voters in swing states.

value.title: Biden paid nearly $300,000 in federal income taxes in 2019
value.excerpt: Joe Biden released his 2019 tax returns on Tuesday, which show he and his wife, Jill, paid nearly $300,000 in federal income tax last year and had an adjusted gross income of about $985,000.

value.title: ABC's Martha Raddatz says she didn't see a lot of 'enthusiasm for Joe Biden' in cross-country trip
value.excerpt: ABC's chief global affairs correspondent Martha Raddatz reports “there wasn't a whole lot of enthusiasm for Joe Biden" during her recent 6,000-mile road trip across America, and that the economy is voters’ main focus.

value.title: Barr accused of 'working hand in glove' with Team Trump, White House
value.excerpt: One former federal prosecutor said of Barr, "The attorney general is working hand in glove with the White House and the Trump re-election campaign."

value.title: Lawyer for Flynn says she updated Trump on status of case

value.title: Trump told group of Christians how he said 'excuse me?' when Mike Pence asked him to pray
value.excerpt: Donald Trump told a group of Christians he said 'excuse me' when Mike Pence asked him to pray with him at their first meeting, a new recording reveals.
